README – Solidification Spreading index
This folder contains the Python code and input data used to compute the solidification/spreading index for the W-Ti-V, W-Ti-Zr, and W-V-Zr ternary systems.
Files
	Solidification_spreading_index.ipynb - Python notebook used for the calculations 
	Thermophysical_Properties_W_V_Ti_Zr.xlsx – elemental thermophysical property inputs 
	WTiV.xlsx – composition list for W-Ti-V, including CALPHAD/Scheil derived TL [K] and TS [K] 
	WTiZr.xlsx – composition list for W-Ti-Zr, including CALPHAD/Scheil derived TL [K] and TS [K] 
	WVZr.xlsx – composition list for W-V-Zr, including CALPHAD/Scheil derived TL [K] and TS [K] 
	HTP_Printability_Results.xlsx – output file generated by the notebook 
What the code does
For each composition, the notebook:
	reads the alloy composition and liquidus/solidus temperatures, 
	computes composition-averaged thermophysical properties, 
	evaluates \tau_1, \tau_2, \tau_{solid}, and \tau_{spread}, 
	computes the solidification/spreading index: 
PI=\tau_{solid}/\tau_{spread}.
Notes
	The calculations were performed using the same workflow for all three ternary systems. 
	If TL [K] and TS [K] are missing, the code uses a fallback estimate. 
	The output workbook contains one sheet per ternary system.
